    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis for hemolysis index predictions",
    "description": "A variance-based Sobol sensitivity analysis was conducted across 8 uncertain input parameters (impeller tip clearance, blood viscosity, inlet velocity profile, turbulence intensity, wall roughness, rotational speed, hematocrit, and power-law hemolysis exponent) using a quasi-Monte Carlo ensemble of 4096 CFD evaluations with a surrogate-accelerated approach. The hemolysis power-law exponent and impeller tip clearance were identified as dominant factors, together accounting for 74% of total output variance in the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH); rotational speed contributed an additional 12%, while remaining parameters each contributed less than 5%. These findings directed targeted experimental validation at the two dominant factor ranges.",
    "method": "Variance-based Sobol indices (first-order and total-effect) via quasi-Monte Carlo sampling with polynomial chaos surrogate",
    "dominantFactors": [
      "hemolysis power-law exponent",
      "impeller tip clearance",
      "rotational speed"
    ],
    "sampleSize": 4096
  },
