      "rationale": "The model form selection is justified through a documented model selection study. The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on its superior performance in separated flows and rotating machinery, confirmed by comparison against the realizable k-epsilon and LES models on the FDA benchmark nozzle (SST k-omega: 7.2% NIH error vs. 14.8% for realizable k-epsilon). The Giersiepen et al. (1990) power-law hemolysis model was selected and its coefficients updated using the Zhang et al. (2011) re-fit. Model form uncertainty was quantified by running three turbulence models and two hemolysis models; the resulting model-form uncertainty contribution to NIH is ±9.1% (95% CI), which is included in the total uncertainty budget.",
