      "rationale": "All model inputs are characterized with documented uncertainty distributions. Blood analog viscosity: measured by cone-and-plate rheometry, mean 3.45 mPa·s, CV 1.8%. Pump geometry: CMM-measured, dimensional tolerances ±0.05 mm. Inlet boundary conditions: derived from PIV measurements with documented uncertainty. Hemolysis model coefficients: probability distributions derived from published literature meta-analysis (Zhang et al. 2011, n=47 data points). Input uncertainty propagation was performed via the Sobol ensemble (4096 runs), fully characterizing the contribution of each input to output uncertainty. All input data are archived and traceable to primary sources.",
